Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.41,0:00:03.14,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It's almost the tenth anniversary of Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.14,0:00:04.88,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}We made it through the first,\Nnow let's aim for the next!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.88,0:00:06.56,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The suspicions become more evident\Nwith the second case.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.56,0:00:10.01,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The distance to something\Nthat shouldn't be real scares them.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.01,0:00:11.59,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.59,0:00:13.38,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.38,0:00:15.27,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.37,0:01:54.48,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}A rich family with a mansion at Shizuoka called us.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.12,0:01:56.78,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}They requested help with their problem:
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.78,0:02:00.81,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}the exorcism of an evil spirit,\Nusing the science of reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.37,0:02:05.13,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}In that mansion, events took place\Nduring the last two years,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.13,0:02:08.47,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}always taking place on the 4th, a {\i1}butsumetsu{\i0} day.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.75,0:02:14.05,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}And when October 4 came along,\Nthe first victim appeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.80,0:02:22.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The deceased is Toshimichi Sekiguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, age 41.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.00,0:02:25.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know if it's suicide or murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.00,0:02:29.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But this card, "Here I pay for my sins from 13 years ago",
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.98,0:02:32.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,may be the key to the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.94,0:02:35.32,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Atsuhiro Kunitomo (56)\NHead of the\NKunitomo Family
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.94,0:02:35.32,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Yasue Kunitomo (42)\NWife of the Head\Nof the Kunitomo Family
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.05,0:02:35.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Thirteen years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.24,0:02:40.53,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Kenzo Akatsuka (50)\NKunitomo Family Butler
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.85,0:02:40.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The master's cruiser{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} san{\r}k into the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.09,0:02:46.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Did the people who died in that accident leave any family here?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.87,0:02:47.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.40,0:03:00.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Please answer me one at a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.98,0:03:04.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Introduce yourself and tell me how you're related to the victims of that shipwreck.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.24,0:03:06.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well then...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.10,0:03:09.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Er... Let's start with Shigeko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.94,0:03:11.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.94,0:03:18.94,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Shigeko Senzaki (52)\NKunitomo Family Housekeeper
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.31,0:03:15.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Shigeko Senzaki, the head housekeeper.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.56,0:03:19.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I lost my husband, who was the chef here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.50,0:03:22.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He was cooking for the cruise.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.80,0:03:28.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My daughter Namika and I\Nwere going to attend too,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.22,0:03:30.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but we both came down with a cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.29,0:03:35.59,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Namika Senzaki (28)\NKunitomo Family Chef
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.29,0:03:35.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After my father died, I took his place here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.13,0:03:41.01,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Masashi Watabiki (28)\NKunitomo Family Chauffeur
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.59,0:03:41.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Masashi Watabiki. I followed in my father's footsteps and became the chauffeur.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.41,0:03:43.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I lost my father in the accident...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.81,0:03:45.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and my younger brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.42,0:03:47.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Two people?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.07,0:03:49.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Er, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.07,0:03:52.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My father was sailing the cruiser,\Nso he had to be there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.17,0:03:58.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But my brother's death seemed especially wrong,\Nsince he'd just happened to tag along for the trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.54,0:04:04.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And the last victim was my wife,\Nwho worked as a maid here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.75,0:04:10.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She was a fine, caring woman\Nwho supported me in my post as butler.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.53,0:04:14.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It... It came as such a shock...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.61,0:04:16.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Akatsuka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.38,0:04:19.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what's the meaning of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.57,0:04:22.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you forcing us to relive that tragedy?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.05,0:04:28.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,To be honest, we suspect one of you\Nmay have murdered Sekiguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.78,0:04:32.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You've gotta admit, you look pretty suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.29,0:04:35.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though you all saw that card\Nwith the "I am the fifth soul" message,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.47,0:04:39.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,none of you mentioned the shipwreck.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.15,0:04:45.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe the rest of you are protecting the murderer!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.60,0:04:47.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,O-Of course not!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.83,0:04:50.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Four people died in that accident, you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.84,0:04:52.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's four souls, not five!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.10,0:04:58.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,One, two, three, four...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.12,0:05:00.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.12,0:05:05.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, the accident occurred\Non September 29, on a {\i1}taian{\i0} day.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.71,0:05:08.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't a {\i1}butsumetsu{\i0} day {\i1}or{\i0} the 4th of a month!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.21,0:05:10.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.07,0:05:15.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think the chef or the housekeeper lady would've been able to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.38,0:05:16.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.36,0:05:17.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.46,0:05:21.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sekiguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was hanged from the balcony!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.71,0:05:26.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right! Namika{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} has acrophobia,\Nso she can't get close to it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.20,0:05:28.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,T-That's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.55,0:05:30.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But what about Shigeko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.41,0:05:34.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The murderer hanged him to make it look like a suicide, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.25,0:05:37.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They'd have to look down from the balcony,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.06,0:05:40.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,to make sure nobody was watching.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.20,0:05:44.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But it'd be really scary for the maid to look straight down from here,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.40,0:05:48.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,because she'd see all the sharp prickly bars of the iron fence below.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.27,0:05:53.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see! Shigeko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is afraid of sharp objects.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.02,0:05:56.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If she were the killer, she'd have hanged him off to the side of the balcony!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.13,0:05:57.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Pretty clever, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.27,0:06:06.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Watabiki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was in the car with the master and mistress during the time of the crime,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.04,0:06:07.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so he couldn't have done it either.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.94,0:06:12.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That leaves just you, Akatsuka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.21,0:06:13.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,N-No...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.99,0:06:15.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think the butler did it either!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.31,0:06:16.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.91,0:06:19.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Take a look at these two cards.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.80,0:06:23.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The printing is slightly crooked, don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.04,0:06:30.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,N-Now that you mention it...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.81,0:06:37.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,An obsessive-compulsive like Akatsuka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nwouldn't do such a sloppy job.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.12,0:06:39.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. But...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.72,0:06:46.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,On the other hand, one of them\Ncould be faking their condition, to fool us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.14,0:06:49.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.19,0:06:50.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,C-Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.50,0:06:53.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.58,0:06:56.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,These quirks and phobias could all be an act.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.94,0:07:03.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Come downstairs with me\Nso I can question you separately!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.60,0:07:05.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll need your fingerprints too...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.88,0:07:07.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,For crying out loud.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.80,0:07:11.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do {\i1}we{\i0} have to get fingerprinted?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.52,0:07:13.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.35,0:07:15.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We need to distinguish your fingerprints from the rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.41,0:07:16.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.60,0:07:20.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Did the suspects have alibis?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.34,0:07:24.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Apart from Watabiki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, the chauffeur, none.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.10,0:07:28.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But we've gotten prints from everyone except the master.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.71,0:07:33.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And we've only found Sekiguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s prints on the rope, so we're kind of at a standstill...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.95,0:07:37.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How come you haven't taken the master's prints yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.21,0:07:38.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.01,0:07:42.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's locked himself on the third floor,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.47,0:07:44.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,saying he won't see anyone until this unlucky day is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.32,0:07:48.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, would you quit this?! Dear?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.75,0:07:50.68,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Calm down, dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.68,0:07:54.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We can talk this over once we learn more...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.40,0:07:57.90,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I'll talk to you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.90,0:07:59.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Dear...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.38,0:08:04.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That...can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.23,0:08:07.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Dear!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.21,0:08:10.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is somebody in there with him?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.01,0:08:15.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's impossible! He said he wasn't going to see anybody, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.56,0:08:19.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Which room is this intercom connected to?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.79,0:08:22.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,O-Our bedroom...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.40,0:08:24.75,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}That's the room where Sekiguchi{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} was hanged.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.25,0:08:26.70,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It's right above {\i1}our{\i0} bedroom!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.02,0:08:29.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.36,0:08:46.24,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}A rope?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.60,0:08:57.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.25,0:09:06.06,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The pills have been crushed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.53,0:09:08.86,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Somebody else {\i1}was{\i0} here...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.05,0:09:12.37,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}But there are no signs of the balcony door being forced open.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.99,0:09:15.67,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}And surely Kunitomo couldn't have forgotten to lock it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.48,0:09:20.15,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}So how did the murderer get inside?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.61,0:09:22.81,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Anyway, I gotta call an ambulance right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.81,0:09:25.49,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Though it may be too late...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.05,0:09:33.11,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}And that rope bugs me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.81,0:09:35.72,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}If my deduction is correct...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.35,0:09:39.70,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}the killer is still...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.80,0:09:42.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.64,0:09:45.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The four-eyed kid went up to the third floor?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.75,0:09:46.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.65,0:09:50.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There was a rope hanging down from the balcony,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.34,0:09:51.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and he climbed it to the third floor!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.80,0:09:52.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.95,0:09:54.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.89,0:09:55.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Open the door!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.89,0:09:56.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.95,0:09:58.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm warning you! Open this door right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.75,0:10:41.25,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10\an8}Intruder alert!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.22,0:10:18.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.52,0:10:21.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, why's that alarm going off?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.74,0:10:22.62,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Did you do something?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.62,0:10:23.75,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Oh, Conan{\rHonorifics - Radio\be10}-kun{\r\be10}?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.00,0:10:25.09,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.46,0:10:28.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad was trying to force the door open
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.09,0:10:30.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and put his finger in the fingerprint reader!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.55,0:10:34.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He forgot that only people who have registered their fingerprints can touch it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.97,0:10:39.05,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Can you stop the alarm and open the door?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.05,0:10:40.21,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Please try!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.21,0:10:42.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay... I'm opening the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.73,0:10:43.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But don't let anybody in except Inspector Yokomizo and old man Mouri.{SAME AS NEXT}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.76,0:10:46.82,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}But don't let anybody in except Inspector Yokomizo and old man Mouri.{SAME AS PREVIOUS}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.45,0:10:50.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You say that, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.36,0:10:53.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,M-Master?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.95,0:10:56.60,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Oh geez, now everybody's coming at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.97,0:11:01.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's not breathing. No pulse either.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.24,0:11:04.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Darling...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.24,0:11:05.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.36,0:11:07.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll call an ambulance!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.08,0:11:09.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll tell the other police officers downstairs...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.58,0:11:10.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.35,0:11:14.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I already called for an ambulance.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.80,0:11:18.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Everybody, just stay put!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.50,0:11:28.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.70,0:11:30.45,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Are you still standing in front of the door?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.45,0:11:33.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.64,0:11:36.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Stay right there and make sure nobody leaves!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.41,0:11:39.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector Yokomizo and Uncle Kogoro,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.96,0:11:44.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,can you check the other rooms to see if there are any signs of a window being forced open?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.91,0:11:46.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.29,0:11:49.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Look over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.64,0:11:54.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Somebody stepped on those pills spilled on the balcony.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.95,0:11:58.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who could've done that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.17,0:12:02.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone deliberately surprised the master, who had heart problems,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.65,0:12:07.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,to give him a heart attack, then crushed his pills so he couldn't take them!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.15,0:12:09.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And this rope!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.15,0:12:12.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The murderer must've used it to make his escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.51,0:12:14.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't moving.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.26,0:12:20.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It took less than a minute for me to find this rope
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.82,0:12:25.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,after hearing the master's cry from the intercom.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.20,0:12:27.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait... You mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.20,0:12:32.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. The murderer saw me climbing up the rope,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.19,0:12:35.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and went back into the room, rather than making a run for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.76,0:12:38.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.10,0:12:41.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If the murderer surprised the master to give him a heart attack,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.48,0:12:45.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,stole his medication and crushed it, tied the rope to the balcony,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.66,0:12:48.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,then watched him die before making an escape,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.80,0:12:50.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,that'd take well over a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.80,0:12:53.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There wasn't time to climb down the rope!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.46,0:12:54.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So there's a good{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} chan{\r}ce...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.49,0:12:59.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,that the murderer is still hiding somewhere on the third floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.23,0:13:05.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,T-Then we should split up and search!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.10,0:13:06.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.32,0:13:08.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.68,0:13:11.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You could be attacked!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.15,0:13:14.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But while we're all standing around, the killer could escape!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.82,0:13:17.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wouldn't it be better for us to search this floor?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.47,0:13:21.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.01,0:13:23.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll search one room at a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.08,0:13:26.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,First I'll enter the room to check the windows.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.14,0:13:28.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The rest of you, follow after me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.97,0:13:34.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} will stake out the hall to make sure no one comes out.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.54,0:13:36.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,U-Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.86,0:13:47.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks fine. Come on in.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.42,0:13:50.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't see anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.51,0:13:52.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Me neither.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.84,0:13:55.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's move on to the next room.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.73,0:14:01.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, we've searched every room, but we haven't found anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.80,0:14:06.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,All the windows on the third floor\Nwere bolted from the inside,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.08,0:14:08.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and there were no signs of forced entry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.53,0:14:14.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Ran! Can you hear me?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.24,0:14:17.18,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Did you see anybody go out the door?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.18,0:14:18.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.66,0:14:22.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Three ambulance crews went in with a stretcher and came out again,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.63,0:14:23.89,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}but that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.12,0:14:26.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That means...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.29,0:14:31.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The kid's got it all wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.86,0:14:33.51,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.51,0:14:36.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, there's one other possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.13,0:14:41.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe the murderer hid among us when Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} opened the door...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.81,0:14:46.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and let the rest of us in!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.23,0:14:48.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It can't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.98,0:14:50.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a sec!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.22,0:14:52.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you saying the killer is among us?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.01,0:14:54.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,N-No...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.49,0:14:58.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We all came running up here when the alarm went off!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.47,0:15:02.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you see us enter after you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.27,0:15:03.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Not really...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.37,0:15:07.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I remember the lady of the house being with us the whole time, but that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.40,0:15:09.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How about you, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.86,0:15:11.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.92,0:15:14.66,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}That's why I wanted to keep the suspects out!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.40,0:15:16.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,At any rate...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.66,0:15:22.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll station officers in front of the fingerprint reader. The third floor will be off-limits.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.24,0:15:25.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,As for all of you, I have more questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.11,0:15:27.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You got that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.48,0:15:35.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When we heard the master's scream over the intercom,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.85,0:15:38.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,his wife was with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.09,0:15:41.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But none of the rest of you have alibis!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.50,0:15:43.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.50,0:15:48.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We were just waiting in our rooms like you told us to!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.50,0:15:50.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We each have a private room.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.09,0:15:55.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't trust us, you should've had somebody guarding us!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.56,0:15:57.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Er, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.60,0:16:01.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The biggest question is how the murderer got inside
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.20,0:16:07.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,after the master said he wouldn't let anyone in for the rest of the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.04,0:16:13.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, when I heard my husband's voice over the intercom,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.06,0:16:17.83,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10\3c&H1F9F&}I'll talk to you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.23,0:16:20.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard something like a knock on the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.00,0:16:25.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And my husband didn't seem surprised by it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.95,0:16:27.33,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}A knock?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.72,0:16:33.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But then he started screaming, like he was in agony!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.20,0:16:35.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,R-Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.25,0:16:39.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe he let somebody in.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.30,0:16:41.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.27,0:16:45.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He kicked out the police who were investigating Sekiguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s hanging
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.82,0:16:47.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and locked himself on the third floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.96,0:16:49.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would he do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.24,0:16:52.89,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Even if that's the case,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.89,0:16:57.98,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}there was some distance in the bedroom between the door and the intercom.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.49,0:17:02.26,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I find it hard to believe that the door opening would scare him enough to {\i1}kill{\i0} him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.06,0:17:05.45,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Even if the murderer had a weapon,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.45,0:17:07.60,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}he had his finger on the intercom,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.60,0:17:10.73,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}so he could've easily called for help\Nand unlocked the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.42,0:17:15.35,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What kind of fear would stop him\Nfrom doing that much?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.24,0:17:18.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's look back at those strange incidents in the past,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.51,0:17:20.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,before we have any {\i1}more{\i0} deaths.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.15,0:17:27.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,First the shipwreck 13 years ago,\Noff the coast of Suruga Bay.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.95,0:17:30.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you recall anything unusual\Nbefore they set sail?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.94,0:17:34.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I went down to the harbor to see everybody off.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.45,0:17:39.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Apart from the fact that Sekiguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r} decided to join them at the last minute,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.45,0:17:41.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't remember anything odd.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.01,0:17:43.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did Sekiguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} suddenly decide to join?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.50,0:17:48.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, he'd been angling to get in on our annual cruise.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.00,0:17:50.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When Namika{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Shigeko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} came down with a cold,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.90,0:17:53.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,we had some extra room, so we agreed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.38,0:17:56.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I remember one strange thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.05,0:18:00.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sekiguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r} brought a huge bag on board!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.61,0:18:03.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Any idea what it was?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.10,0:18:07.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I think he said it was full of scuba-diving equipment.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.43,0:18:09.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.92,0:18:13.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So, the people who died in the shipwreck were...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.63,0:18:19.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Shigeko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s husband and Namika{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s father, who was the family chef...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.07,0:18:25.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Watabiki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s father, who was the chauffeur...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.68,0:18:30.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Watabiki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s younger brother,\Nwho was a guest on the cruise...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.78,0:18:36.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and Akatsuka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s wife,\Nwho was a maid here, am I right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.75,0:18:37.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.99,0:18:44.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You, your husband and Sekiguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nsurvived by getting into a life raft.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.30,0:18:46.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Were there any other rafts on the ship?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.30,0:18:48.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There were,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.56,0:18:54.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but we were so desperate to escape that we never saw whether anyone got into them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.01,0:18:56.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't even know if anyone sent a distress call.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.80,0:19:02.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,More recently, the master had a nightmare, the car almost crashed,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.35,0:19:06.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,this strange card was delivered to the house, a cupboard fell in the middle of the night,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.74,0:19:09.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and strange sounds were heard in the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.91,0:19:12.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't any of you notice these things always happened
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.89,0:19:15.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,on the 4th of a month, on an unlucky {\i1}butsumetsu{\i0} day?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.76,0:19:19.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We did notice it was always on the 4th.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.72,0:19:23.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The master may have figured it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.18,0:19:26.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He was very picky about dates.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.28,0:19:29.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He always chose a lucky {\i1}taian{\i0} day for the cruise.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.15,0:19:34.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And Sekiguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r} was always at the house the day before an incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.90,0:19:42.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Was he there on the night the two of them heard strange sounds in the empty house?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.19,0:19:43.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.75,0:19:44.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ma'am?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.79,0:19:48.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of sounds?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.17,0:19:49.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.94,0:19:54.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was like something bouncing off the wall...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.95,0:19:58.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and slapping against leather.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.13,0:20:02.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds like somebody throwing a ball against a wall and catching it in a baseball glove.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.40,0:20:04.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Does anyone in this house play baseball?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.59,0:20:07.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.32,0:20:09.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, not now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.32,0:20:11.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But my late brother was a baseball player.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.63,0:20:12.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Wait a minute...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.85,0:20:15.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then it...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.39,0:20:17.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then it {\i1}is{\i0} a ghost!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.97,0:20:22.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The nightmare happened in bed,\Nwhich a maid makes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.54,0:20:24.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The car represents the chauffeur.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.40,0:20:27.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The cupboard goes with the chef.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.51,0:20:30.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And the sound of someone playing baseball...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.30,0:20:35.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Each incident is connected\Nto one of the accident victims!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.64,0:20:44.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then the message, "Repent of your sins before I awaken"...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.00,0:20:46.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,means their ghosts will arise to haunt this house!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.57,0:20:52.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ma'am? Ma'am, are you all right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.76,0:20:54.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I-It's a curse!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.63,0:20:59.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This house is haunted by an evil spirit!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.39,0:21:01.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.13,0:21:03.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no such thing as ghosts!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.78,0:21:09.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,B-But only a ghost could slip past that electronic security system!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.65,0:21:13.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right... The master must've seen a ghost!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.90,0:21:17.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you kidding? Yokomizo, tell her she's being—
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.09,0:21:23.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.65,0:21:28.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My cell phone started vibrating at the perfect moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.90,0:21:30.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yokomizo speaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.18,0:21:31.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.59,0:21:33.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Forensics...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.35,0:21:37.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You found fingerprints on the rope and the medicine bottle?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.05,0:21:39.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.42,0:21:41.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.18,0:21:46.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And you're sure they're the prints\Nof the last person who touched them?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.85,0:21:49.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The case is as good as solved!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.89,0:21:53.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We have everyone's prints!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.38,0:21:56.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well? Whose prints did they find?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.34,0:21:57.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,W-W-Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.89,0:22:06.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,T-They don't belong to anyone who works here.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.30,0:22:08.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's crazy!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.55,0:22:13.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then how'd the murderer get past that door?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.72,0:22:15.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.57,0:22:17.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a ghost...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.97,0:22:20.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a ghost after all...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.06,0:22:26.80,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}This just got interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.68,0:24:00.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The president of the company disappeared on September 26, 13 years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.19,0:24:04.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If that's all, I'd like to get back to work!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.15,0:24:07.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you see anybody new or not?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.60,0:24:10.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,W-We didn't...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.25,0:24:13.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, there was an extra person.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.04,0:24:16.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, allow me to explain...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.09,0:24:19.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,how the two murders in this mansion really happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.58,0:24:25.05,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.42,0:24:30.05,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's Hint:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.42,0:24:30.05,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Siblings
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.16,0:24:31.12,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, the solution!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.12,0:24:33.04,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,But if it really was the work of a ghost...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.04,0:24:33.85,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.85,0:24:34.68,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Ow.
